### 1979 Assault on the American Embassy in Pakistan

*   Main article: [1979 United States Embassy burning in Islamabad](/1979_United_States_Embassy_burning_in_Islamabad)

The fervor spilled beyond Iran's borders. On November 21, 1979, the [Embassy of the United States in Islamabad](/Embassy_of_the_United_States,_Islamabad) was attacked and burned by a mob of Pakistani students, incited by the Iran crisis. Khomeini, falsely claiming the U.S. and [Israel](/Israel) were behind the [Grand Mosque seizure](/Grand_Mosque_seizure) in Saudi Arabia, played a role in fanning the flames. Four embassy personnel died in the ensuing chaos. Pakistan's president, [Muhammad Zia-ul-Haq](/Zia-ul-Haq), condemned the attack and deployed the army to quell the rioters.

